columns.name: launch_template_name
columns.description: The name of the launch template.

columns.name: launch_template_id
columns.description: The ID of the launch template.

columns.name: create_time
columns.description: The time the version was created.

columns.name: created_by
columns.description: The principal that created the version.

columns.name: default_version
columns.description: Indicates whether the version is the default version.

columns.name: disable_api_stop
columns.description: Indicates whether the instance is enabled for stop protection.

columns.name: disable_api_termination
columns.description: If set to true, indicates that the instance cannot be terminated using the Amazon EC2 console, command line tool, or API.

columns.name: ebs_optimized
columns.description: Indicates whether the instance is optimized for Amazon EBS I/O.

columns.name: image_id
columns.description: The ID of the AMI or a Systems Manager parameter.

columns.name: kernel_id
columns.description: The ID of the kernel, if applicable.

columns.name: key_name
columns.description: The name of the key pair.

columns.name: ram_disk_id
columns.description: The ID of the RAM disk, if applicable.

columns.name: user_data
columns.description: The user data of the launch template.
